lzh_formatted:
  title: 腰箴
  author: 李奎報
  language: lzh
  text: 常直不弓。被人怒嗔。能曲如磬。遠辱於身。惟人禍福。係爾屈伸。
korean:
  title: 요잠
  author: 이규보
  language: kor
  text: 항상 뻣뻣하여 굽힐 줄을 모르다가는 남에게 성냄을 당하게 된다. 능히 굽히기를, 경(磬) 쇠 덩어리 같게 하여야 몸에 욕이 미치지 아니하느니라. 대개 사람의 화복(禍福)이란 너[腰]의 굽힘과 뻣뻣한 데에 매인 것이다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0520_030_0020&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: On the Waist
  author: Lee Gyubo
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Stand always rigid, unbending,
    and you shall face the anger of others.
    But learn to bend like the sonorous bell,
    and shame will never touch your body.
    For human fortune and ruin alike
    rest upon the yielding and the stiff—
    upon the bending of your waist.
  footnotes:
    - The 'waist' (腰) serves as a metaphor for flexibility of spirit and humility in human affairs. The sonorous bell (磬) is an ancient musical instrument whose sound depends on its shape and how it receives the striker—a symbol of wise receptivity.
